.TH "TOUCH.TOUCHTYPE" "3JS" "February 10, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Touch.touchType \- Touch: touchType property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]touchType\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]Touch\f[R] interface returns the type of device that triggered the
touch, such as a stylus, or direct touch from a finger.
.SH VALUE
A string from the \f[CR]TouchType\f[R] enumeration.
Possible values are:
.TP
\f[B]\(dqdirect\(dq\f[R]
The touch was made by a direct contact, such as a finger on the screen.
.TP
\f[B]\(dqstylus\(dq\f[R]
The touch was made using a stylus or pen device.
.SH EXAMPLE
.SS Basic usage
.IP
.EX
someElement.addEventListener(
  \(dqtouchstart\(dq,
  (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    \f[B]for\f[R] (\f[B]const\f[R] touch \f[B]of\f[R] event.changedTouches) {
      console.log(\(gaTouch type: ${touch.touchType}\(ga);

      \f[B]if\f[R] (touch.touchType === \(dqstylus\(dq) {
        \f[I]// Handle stylus\-specific input, such as altitude and azimuth angles.\f[R]
        console.log(\(gaaltitudeAngle: ${touch.altitudeAngle}\(ga);
        console.log(\(gaazimuthAngle: ${touch.azimuthAngle}\(ga);
      }
    }
  },
  \f[B]false\f[R],
);
.EE
